text.section:
The sentencing judge shall study the record of all persons petitioning for parole and, in his discretion, may:
Cause additional background or character information to be collected or reduced to writing by the Department of Corrections;
Conduct hearings on the desirability of granting parole;
Impose on the parolee the conditions he sees fit;
Order the granting of parole;
Issue warrants for persons when there is reason to believe they have violated the conditions of their parole and conduct hearings on such matters;
Determine the period of supervision for parolees, which period may be subject to extension or reduction;
Grant final discharge to parolees.
